title: For Sale:  For sale, Original WWI German M1915 "WÜRTTEMBERG" EM/NCO's Buckle and Belt
postcontent:
For sale, Original WWI German M1915 "WÜRTTEMBERG" EM/NCO's Belt Buckle. (Koppelschloß) with original leather tab on buckle and original leather belt. Buckle is the more desirable steel construction, slightly convex stamped steel box-buckle, painted in a flat feldgrau, shows some rust, but overall in very good – excellent condition, featuring the coat of arms of the state of Württemberg to its domed center, encompassed by a dual rope-like border within which, against a ribbed background, is "Furchtlos Und Trew" (Fearless And Loyal) with a six-pointed star to the base. On the reverse of the buckle may be seen a metal prong bar with dual prongs, for the retaining tongue of a belt, as well as the buckle catch, with the original leather fob still attached, has a slight tear in the leather. Original leather rough side out belt is in excellent used condition, with the steel retaining tongue, marked size “105”. The Kingdom of Württemberg was one of the few States to retain its own distinctive buckle designs until the end of the First World War in 1918. Most of the other States ended up adopting the Prussian style buckle. 

Selling for $275.00 FTF Frisco, Texas, or will ship, buyer pays for shipping and insurance, US Postal Money Order only.

title: For Sale:  Savage .308 Bolt Action/Precision work
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Savage Axis chambered in .308 Winchester. It sits in the limited edition Moon Harvest camo stock and has probably seen less than 50 rounds.

The major flaw with the Axis series is the wimpy flexible stock and stiff trigger. I have addressed these issues by reinforcing the fore-end of the stock with epoxy and aluminum flat bar. There are a total of 6 aluminum reinforcements in the stock now. The gaps around the trigger guard on the stock have been filled to eliminate side to side give as well. The trigger has been set at 2.8 lbs and the trigger has been reshaped into a flat bar design that allows for more sensitivity in the finger tip-overall better trigger pulls leading to more accurate shots! I have done what Savage should have done from the factory. Way better performer now, will shoot 1 moa at 100 easily. Custom gun work can cost a lot of money, save here with a great deal on a light weight bolt action that will deliver awesome performance for a budget.

No scope is included. The rings and mount however is.

Below are a list of things that has brought this Axis up to the rest of the competition:
Aluminum pillar bedding added to fore-stock
